  <front>
   <head>[Tophet] Inscription on a Portrait</head>
  </front>
  <body>
   <lg xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" type="poem">
    <lg n="1" stanza_type="octet">
     <l n="1" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">Such Tophet was; so looked the grinning fiend</l>
     <l n="2" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">Whom many a frighted prelate called his friend;</l>
     <l n="3" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">I saw them bow and, while they wished him dead,</l>
     <l n="4" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">With servile simper nod the mitred head.</l>
     <l n="5" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">Our Mother-Church with half-averted sight</l>
     <l n="6" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">Blushed as she blessed her grisly proselyte:</l>
     <l n="7" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">Hosannahs rung through Hell's tremendous borders,</l>
     <l n="8" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">And Satan's self had thoughts of taking orders.</l>
    </lg>
   </lg>
